@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home - Blazor WebAssembly starter</PageTitle>

<div class="pageStyle h-100 d-flex justify-content-center">
    <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-xl-2 h-100">
        <div class="col d-flex flex-column justify-content-xl-center order-last order-xl-first">
            <div class="title">Blazor WebAssembly starter</div>
            <div class="subTitle">This Visual Studio template gives you a client-side Blazor app with a full chrome layout, sample routes, and a switchable theme system - ready to extend.</div>

            <div class="mt-4 homeCopy">
                <h2 class="h5 text-uppercase text-secondary mb-2">Quick start</h2>
                <p class="mb-2">From the project directory, run <code>dotnet run</code>. Then open <a href="http://localhost:5070/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">http://localhost:5070/</a> (default <code>http</code> profile in <code>Properties/launchSettings.json</code>). The <code>https</code> profile also listens on HTTP port 5070.</p>

                <h2 class="h5 text-uppercase text-secondary mt-4 mb-2">What this template provides</h2>
                <ul class="ps-3 mb-0 lh-lg">
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Blazor WebAssembly</strong> targeting <strong>.NET 10</strong>, with <code>HttpClient</code> registered and scoped to the app base address for static files under <code>wwwroot</code> or future APIs.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Layout</strong>: <code>TopNavLayout</code> with a responsive Bootstrap navbar (including a <strong>dropdown</strong> example), main content area, and footer.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Sample pages</strong>: <strong>Counter</strong> (component state and events), <strong>Weather</strong> (<code>GetFromJsonAsync</code> against <code>sample-data/weather.json</code>), and <strong>Themes</strong> (live theme switching).</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>Theming</strong>: <code>ThemeService</code> plus <code>wwwroot/js/theme.js</code> and <code>wwwroot/css/themes.css</code> expose palette CSS variables (e.g. <code>--cf-indigo-core</code>) and multiple named themes.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>UI stack</strong>: Bootstrap&nbsp;5, Bootstrap Icons, Devicons, and Google Fonts (Bebas Neue / Montserrat) wired in <code>wwwroot/index.html</code>.</li>
                    <li><strong>Routing</strong>: <code>App.razor</code> uses a default layout and a <strong>Not Found</strong> page for unknown routes.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-4 homeCopy">
                <p class="mb-2">Try the sample routes:</p>
                <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                    <NavLink class="btn btn-primary rounded" href="/counter">Counter</NavLink>
                    <NavLink class="btn btn-primary rounded" href="/weather">Weather</NavLink>
                    <NavLink class="btn btn-primary rounded" href="/themes">Themes</NavLink>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-3 homeCopy">
                <span>Built with pride using:</span>
                <div class="hstack my-2">
                    <div><i class="devicons devicon-csharp-plain colored me-1"></i></div>
                    <div><i class="devicons devicon-bootstrap-plain colored me-1"></i></div>
                    <div><i class="devicons devicon-javascript-plain colored me-1"></i></div>
                    <div><i class="devicons devicon-html5-plain colored me-1"></i></div>
                    <div><i class="devicons devicon-css3-plain colored me-1"></i></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col d-flex flex-column justify-content-center">
            <img src="/images/LandingPageLogo.png" class="img-fluid" alt="Home page logo" />
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
